4 Material design method The material design optimization problem consists of ﬁnding a distribution of material inside the unit cell that will achieve speciﬁed homogenized properties. This problem is also known as the inverse homogenization problem (Cherkaev 2000; Sigmund 1994; Bendsøe and Sigmund 2003). The optimization problem consists of minimizing a cost function related to the density distribution inside the unit cell subjected to equality constraints on the elastic properties. Thus, the optimization problem can be stated in continuous form as follows (Sigmund 1994, 1995):
