8.2 Homogenization of FGM unit cells To illustrate the potentiality of the method, some twodimensional (2-D) FGM composite unit cells (Y = [0, 1] × [0, 1]) with two-dimensional gradation were homogenized. The same homogenized properties were used as input for the material design problem in Section 4 to check its capability to recover the material distribution. 8.2.1 Example 1 – trigonometric material gradation The ﬁrst gradation law considered (for the pseudodensity) is given by: ρ (x, y) = (sin 2π x sin 2π y + 1) /2 and 0 ≤ x ≤ 1; 0 ≤ y ≤ 1. as shown in Fig. 11a. (41)

