Appendix A: H-S upper and lower limits For isotropic materials, the upper and lower limits of H-S are given as a function of the bulk modulus (K) and shear modulus (G). Thus, considering two isotropic materials indicated by superscripts (+) and (−), whose properties follow the relation K+ > K− and G+ > G− , the upper and lower limits for the bulk modulus, Kmax and Kmin , respectively, are given by (Hashin and Shtrikman 1963; Bendsøe and Sigmund 2003): (1 − ρ) ρ K+ − K− Kmax = (1−ρ) K +ρ K − (1 − ρ) K+ + ρ K− + G+
